Tho,&#8217; truth to be told, it doesn&#8217;t seem to matter (at least in my experience) whether you actually explicitly follow a recipe &#8230; the important thing is to have it in a salted brine water for a decent interval of time. You can use your favorite herbs (I like thyme and sage) if you don&#8217;t like rosemary, for instance. Or, hey &#8211; add them all!! <img src='http://static.thepioneerwoman.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif' alt=':D' class='wp-smiley' /> .</p>
