	<div class="comment even depth-2" id="comment-2056373">
		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number"></p>
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a6081d057ca2aff2e7e15763e05b229d?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>KB <span>On Tuesday, October 26 at 4:35 pm</span></h4>
			<p>Brining a thawed utility turkey that is not butter injected works beautifully.  I have been brining for the last three years and it improves the meat so much I would not consider skipping the process. </p>
<p>If you are using a Butterball or pre-basted turkey there is no need to brine as the salt in the butter has a similar effect as soaking in salt water.</p>
