	<div class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2140330">
		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number"></p>
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/9949c9020ae542d50f13c06f6f301f08?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>Marc <span>On Sunday, November 21 at 9:29 am</span></h4>
			<p>Becareful using a garbage white garbage bag for your turkey brining. Nowadays they are using chemicals to keep garbage oders down which will contaminate your turkey and even possibly cause illness. I am a deer hunter and I usally debone the deer before I take it to the meat market to have them make it it into Summer Sausage or jerky. I have for years put the meat into black trash bags and last year they refused to take it because of the reasons I gave above. So just a word of caution.</p>
