		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number">37</p>
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3bdacbfed9df7a806f6c3254864856d2?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>Pola <span>On Tuesday, October 26 at 7:39 am</span></h4>
			<p>Thanks, Ree, for the recipe.  I am going to do this for Thanksgiving.</p>
<p>About the bag, maybe this will help.  I brined a turkey a few years ago and I did not use a bag at all but instead stood it up inside a tall stockpot and then poured the brine over it.  I then put the cover on the pot and stuck the whole thing in the fridge.  The brine completely enveloped the turkey and then there was no need for turning it.  </p>
<p>Just an idea that worked for me.  <img src='http://static.thepioneerwoman.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' />   Hope it helps.</p>
					</div>
