			<h4>Vicki in GA <span>On Tuesday, October 26 at 10:37 am</span></h4>
			<p>Don&#8217;t worry about brining &#8211; for one thing it kills bacteria rather than encourages it to grow.<br />
I&#8217;m Jewish and for many many years we brine (Kosher) meat in salt and spices to remove the nasties.  Also, brining tends to make the meat more tender because of the salt and sugar.  Our grannies brined and their grannie brined &#8211; we&#8217;re all here to tell about it.  My suggestion is to buy a fresh turkey from your butcher, rather than a frozen bird.</p>
