		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number">88</p>
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e26c94186afabb640d0ee83bf41896b9?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>Laura K <span>On Tuesday, October 26 at 10:59 am</span></h4>
			<p>Alton Brown from food network has a great solution for brining a turkey if you don&#8217;t have room in your fridge to keep it.  I never do.  I got one of those big yellow drink coolers that sports teams and construction workers use and you put the turkey and ice in there and add your brine.  It stays cold the entire time without having to keep it in your fridge.  I use it several times a year and that is all I use it for.  It was a great investment!</p>
					</div>
