	<div class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2056691">
		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number"></p>
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/698bbb2a634377e70f07e6eaa9c8342c?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>Cathy C <span>On Thursday, October 28 at 1:27 pm</span></h4>
			<p>A shot of bourbon?!  We use 1/2 a bottle!  Woo Hoo talk about flavorful and the alcohol cooks off!  We use a heavy duty black garbage bag placed inside an ice chest.  Tie real tight and toss a bag of ice on.  Brine overnight.</p>
<p>For those looking for a new way to cook turkey:<br />
Melt 1 stick of butter<br />
blend in 1/2 cup all purpose flour<br />
Pat mixture on the brined turkey.  Bake at 450 until golden then turn down to 300.  Baste with a water with a couple of tbls. of melted butter until you have drippings, then use the,<br />
You get a turkey with a crust like fried chicken. SUPER moist and wonderful!</p>
					</div>
